- Use basis set path inside the Molecul::Factory ... don't burden the user.
- Matrix3D/Vecor3D and the 2D version.  Should these all be covnverted to blaze::StaticXXXX.   By defualt blaze does some
  fancey memory alignment magic they may help performance.
  Types.C add mat3d_t and rmat3d_t for consistency.
-we now have tiny diffs in three submodules: blaze, wignerSymbols and libxc.  Part of this is suppressing
CMake noise about Min versions.  Maybe there is a better way to deal with this.  Tow other are compiler warnings in blaze and time stamped xc.h for useless recompile in libxc.  How to the deal with this?  Keep a patch and apply it after checkout?

The cause: submodules/libxc/CMakeLists.txt localizes the <xc_version.h> include in xc.h via an unconditional file(WRITE), which bumps xc.h's mtime on every cmake reconfigure. So every CMakeLists edit (constant during dev) forced Libxc_LDA_Exchange.C to recompile. Patched to write-only-if-content-changed (matching what configure_file does for config.h). Verified: two forced reconfigures now leave xc.h's mtime untouched and Libxc is not rebuilt.


