#### Bug

- Bug From another session:DFT fit-basis leak (found via ASan 2026-06-20): the DFT Hamiltonian builds a CD fit basis
  (`BasisSet::CreateCDFitBasisSet` -> `EFit_IBS`) that is never freed -- LSan shows the fit-basis
  radials leaking on water_DFT (old PG ~1.6MB / 21k allocs, new PG1 ~0.6MB). The HF path is
  leak-clean. Pre-existing in BOTH trees (shared Hamiltonian/fit-basis ownership), not the PG
  refactor. Fix: pin down who owns the result of CreateCDFitBasisSet and ensure ~Ham_DFT_U (or the
  SCFIterator) deletes it.


