### Code review comments

- "APW_IBS is an IrrepBasisSet<dcmplx> sibling of PlaneWave_IBS — same base interface — but deliberately not an Orbital_1E_IBS, because APW's overlap is energy-dependent." 
Answer: we have to solve a nonline sec equation by iterating:
guess E₀, build H(E₀), O(E₀);
solve the linear generalized problem H(E₀)c = ε·O(E₀)c → eigenvalues ε_n(E₀);
pick the relevant ε_n =: E₁, set E₀ ← E₁, repeat until E₁ = E₀ (the fixed point ε_n(E*) = E*).
Its almost like a SCF iterator except 1) we finding E* instead of a converged charge density and 2) S(E) also changes with each iteration just the H.

My view of this higher mid level plan is now 1) GO suitably far along Lineage A and B. 2) For lineage A create a generic template <isM_1E_Evalualtor E> class EPlaneWave_IBS<E> and start migrating the hard coded PW IBSs one at a time.  Most code and member data moves into the evaluators.  3) Figure how to graft this process onto the lineage B versions.    4) Start thinking about e-e repulsion, this requires a top level DFT upgrade first, and I am specing that out now.

What about GPW after FLAPW ... we already have integral engines in src/BasisSet/Molecule if that helps

"How should the PW complex density handle DM_CD's Gaussian/HF/fit-only methods (AccumulateDirect/Exchange, GetRepulsion3C, FitGetConstraint) that plane waves never use?"  
- We will need to somehow split up tDM_CD into 1E, DFT and HF mixin versions along the same lines as for basis functions.
  This is exactly the sort refactoring I want to discover.  What are the correct abstractions for a clean implentation
  of everything {atom/molecule/Lattice_3D//Lattice_2D//Lattice_1D}*{1E,DFT,HF}*{Pol,unPol}

Is virtual hmat_t<T> MakeExternalPotential(const Structure*) const=0; the analogue of MakeNuclear in the atom/moleulce parts of BasisSet?  If so we now have three names for the what I think are the same thing: ExternalPotential, Ven, and Nuclear.   I don't like ExternalPotential.  External to what?  All those nuclei are *in* the lattice.  I see External and I think of an EM field origininating from outside the NxNxN lattice.  

-Pin list:  Review ElConfig and electron dumping. 




